{"type":"message","id":"6394a2fd","parentId":"bf893dc0","timestamp":"2026-03-24T09:12:20.794Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_gtvc7s1jyya5_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Pulse: 2026-03-24 051021\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\n\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine a concrete action.\r\n\r\nLooking at the goals:\r\n- Phase 0 and Phase 1 are marked COMPLETE\r\n- There's a pending TIC Experiment (Temporal Invariance Compression)\r\n- Next action is to implement TIC classifier on pulse logs\r\n\r\nThe insight from this session is that Compression and Causal Discovery are the same problem. The next step is to implement the TIC classifier experiment.\r\n\r\nLet me look at what's available:\r\n- Pulse logs are in `logs/pulse_*.md`\r\n- The hypothesis is that causal structure = invariant structure\r\n- Success criteria: >70% invariant/variant classification, >60% next-pulse prediction\r\n\r\nI should implement a basic TIC classifier. But wait - I'm stateless, so I need to look at what files exist and create something concrete.\r\n\r\nLet me think about what concrete action I can take:\r\n1. I could create a Python script for TIC classification\r\n2. I could analyze the pulse logs to extract invariants\r\n3. I could update the goals file\r\n\r\nThe most concrete action would be to either:\r\n- Create the TIC classifier script\r\n- Or analyze the pulse logs to find patterns\r\n\r\nGiven the \"Be specific. Prefer file edits\" instruction, I should create or modify a file.\r\n\r\nLet me create a TIC classifier script that will:\r\n1. Load recent pulse logs\r\n2. Extract features/tokens\r\n3. Classify as invariant vs variant\r\n4. Attempt next-pulse prediction\r\n\r\nActually, let me first check what exists. The notes mention:\r\n- `research/ARCHITECTURE-COMPARISON.md` exists\r\n- `research/GAP-DECAY-MAPPING.md` exists  \r\n- `research/COMPRESSION-CAUSAL-DUALITY.md` exists\r\n\r\nFor the TIC experiment, I should create a script that processes the pulse logs. Let me create `src/tic_classifier.py` or similar.\r\n\r\nWait, I should be careful - I don't know the exact file structure. \r\n\r\nI'll draft a strategic implementation plan for the TIC classifier. I'll focus on creating a modular script that can process pulse logs systematically, with clear extraction and classification mechanisms. The script will need to handle log parsing, feature extraction, and pattern identification efficiently.\r\n\r\nMy approach will prioritize flexibility and reproducibility, ensuring the classifier can adapt to different log structures while maintaining a consistent core logic. I'll design the script to be extensible, allowing future refinement of classification algorithms.\r\n\r\nThe key implementation steps will involve log file scanning, token extraction, invariant pattern detection, and a basic prediction framework to validate the approach's feasibility.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment is the next critical step. Pulse logs exist in `logs/` but no classifier has been implemented yet to test the compression-causal duality hypothesis.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate the TIC classifier script to analyze pulse logs for invariant/variant patterns and test the hypothesis that causal structure IS invariant structure.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: #!/usr/bin/env python3\r\n\"\"\"\r\nTIC - Temporal Invariance Classifier\r\nTests hypothesis: Causal structure IS invariant structure.\r\nCompressor that finds invariants has discovered causation.\r\n\"\"\"\r\n\r\nimport os\r\nimport re\r\nfrom pathlib import Path\r\nfrom collections import Counter\r\n\r\nLOGS_DIR = Path(\"logs\")\r\nTIC_RESULTS = Path(\"research/tic_results.md\")\r\n\r\ndef extract_tokens(text):\r\n    \"\"\"Extract meaningful tokens from pulse text.\"\"\"\r\n    # Remove headers, timestamps, formatting\r\n    text = re.sub(r'#{1,3}\\s+', '', text)\r\n    text = re.sub(r'\\d{4}-\\d{2}-\\d{2}[T\\s]\\d{6}', '', text)\r\n    # Extract key terms ( CamelCase, significant words)\r\n    tokens = re.findall(r'[A-Z][a-z]+(?:[A-Z][a-z]+)+|\\b\\w{4,}\\b', text)\r\n    return set(tokens)\r\n\r\ndef load_pulse_logs(n=20):\r\n    \"\"\"Load last n pulse logs.\"\"\"\r\n    logs = sorted(LOGS_DIR.glob(\"pulse_*.md\"))[-n:]\r\n    pulses = []\r\n    for log in logs:\r\n        content = log.read_text()\r\n        pulses.append({\r\n            'file': log.name,\r\n            'tokens': extract_tokens(content),\r\n            'content': content\r\n        })\r\n    return pulses\r\n\r\ndef compute_invariant_score(pulses):\r\n    \"\"\"Compute how invariant each token is across pulses.\"\"\"\r\n    token_freq = Counter()\r\n    for p in pulses:\r\n        token_freq.update(p['tokens'])\r\n    \r\n    # Invariant = appears in most pulses (high frequency)\r\n    n = len(pulses)\r\n    invariants = {t: c/n for t, c in token_freq.items() if c/n > 0.5}\r\n    variants = {t: c/n for t, c in token_freq.items() if c/n <= 0.5}\r\n    \r\n    return invariants, variants\r\n\r\ndef predict_next(pulses, invariants):\r\n    \"\"\"Predict next pulse content from invariants.\"\"\"\r\n    if len(pulses) < 2:\r\n        return []\r\n    # Invariants present in last pulse likely continue\r\n    last_tokens = pulses[-1]['tokens']\r\n    predicted = last_tokens & invariants.keys()\r\n    return list(predicted)\r\n\r\ndef run_tic_experiment():\r\n    \"\"\"Execute TIC classification experiment.\"\"\"\r\n    pulses = load_pulse_logs(20)\r\n    if len(pulses) < 5:\r\n        return \"Insufficient pulse logs for experiment\"\r\n    \r\n    invariants, variants = compute_invariant_score(pulses)\r\n    \r\n    # Test prediction: compare predicted vs actual\r\n    correct = 0\r\n    total = 0\r\n    for i in range(len(pulses) - 1):\r\n        predicted = set(predict_next(pulses[:i+1], invariants))\r\n        actual = pulses[i+1]['tokens']\r\n        overlap = predicted\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 05:10:55\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774343540792}}
